<HEADLINE>
FT  20 NOV 93 / Finance and the Family: Building societies attract Pounds
258m of net funds - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Building societies attracted Pounds 258m of net funds last month - just over
double the net inflow in September, which ended three months of net
outflows. Commenting on the relatively subdued inflow at a time of the year
when people traditionally build up savings to finance Christmas spending,
Adrian Coles, association director-general, highlighted the stiff
competition for retail funds at a time of low interest rates. He said postal
savings accounts had been particularly successful in attracting customers.
