<HEADLINE>
FT  20 NOV 93 / International Company News: Diversification leaves Minebea
with net loss
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By WILLIAM DAWKINS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MINEBEA, the world's leading maker of miniature ball bearings, lifted
operating profits, but suffered heavy losses from diversifying into
semiconductors, writes William Dawkins.
Pre-tax profits rose 8.5 per cent to Y8.93bn (Dollars 83.5m) in the year to
end-September, on sales up fractionally to Y201.6bn. It swung from a net
profit of Y2.73bn last year into a net loss of Y59.75bn.
It will pay no dividend this year, having paid Y6 per share in 1992.
