<HEADLINE>
FT  20 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Ross warns of Pounds 2m non-recurring
charge
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Ross Group dived 6p to 16p yesterday as the industrial holding
company warned that profits for the current year would be below earlier
expectations, after charging non-recurring costs of at least Pounds 2m for
restructuring.
The company said trading conditions in October were worse than expected and
with the exception of Gemini and Tadmod where growth had continued, measures
had been and continued to be taken to reduce further overheads, albeit at a
substantial short term cost.
The company yesterday completed the purchase of Cascade and Keenon from
Tomei of Hong Kong for Pounds 4m, payable by the issue of 13.3m new ordinary
shares at 30p. In addition, Tomei has subscribed for a further 2.33m shares
in Ross also at 30p.
