<HEADLINE>
FT  20 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Telspec pathfinder prospectus out
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TELSPEC, the fast-growing Rochester-based manufacturer of sophisticated
electronic telecommunications equipment, which is coming to market next
month, issued its pathfinder prospectus yesterday. The placing is likely to
value the company at more than Pounds 40m.
The group designs and manufactures advanced equipment which enables
customers like BT, Telecom Australia and Deutsche Telekom, to improve the
efficiency of their networks and reduces the cost of installing or expanding
local telephone services.
In the year to December 31, Telspec, which has manufacturing operations in
the UK and Australia, reported pre-tax profits of Pounds 3.36m on turnover
of Pounds 18.2m. In the first half of the current year, pre-tax profits of
Pounds 1.94m were reported on turnover of Pounds 8.53m.
The flotation is expected to raise about Pounds 5m for the company, which
will be used to fund increased capital expenditure and expand overseas
service and support facilities.
