</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Lynx Holdings reported a jump in pre-tax profits from Pounds 115,000 to
Pounds 619,000 for the half year to September 30.
At the same time the supplier of computer services and leisure products
announced two acquisitions financed by a placing and open offer.
The shares rose by 8p to close at 45p.
